Class ModelRuleAction

java.lang.Object
  edu.nyu.cs.omnidroid.ui.simple.model.ModelItem
      edu.nyu.cs.omnidroid.ui.simple.model.ModelRuleAction

public class ModelRuleAction
extends ModelItem

An instance of an action whose data has been set by the end-user. When a user picks a ModelAction to be executed by a rule, we prompt them for input data about how to execute the action. Their supplied information is stored in mActionDatas and the original action type is stored in mModelAction. So this class contains the action template, and whatever data the user supplied for it.
